Maybe it's just an incubator. That's what I keep coming back to. It's a space that helps musicians cultivate their own personal brand. It doesn't market for them, but instead develops the tools that help musicians market themselves?
Like the idea is:
- central space that has all the tools to teach lessons
- Rent out a room for lessons period, part of the payment goes towards the studio (automatic and online)
	- Have musicians sign up?
- Musicians can pay for credits that teach them marketing and sales skills and leadership skills
- Expect the artists to find their own students

Not masturbating is changing the landscape of my horniness. Like...increasing it. Sometimes to incredibly high levels. I saw this woman in the lobby of Starbucks, nothing special about her. She was blonde and  wore a black hoodie and Lululemon leggings with black Hokas. I couldn't take my eyes off her. And the whole time, there was this strong desire to do something about it. To masturbate. To store it for later so I had something to think about when I got home. 

It's made me think a lot about the world I've missed out on by being so addicted. I've seen it as so normal, as a way of relieving stress or getting ready for bed or even just an escape for spiritual fantasies in things I feel unfilfilled by. In changing that, I feel like I'm about to experience love, especially sexual intimacy, as something that *doesn't have to be dealt with* and can just exist. At least, I'm hoping for that. And I'm hoping it changes my relationship with people, from looking for things to put into the spank bank to cultivating real intimacy, and also to stop being afraid of the intimacy I have with my family.

I think I'm overeating as withdrawals. Really trying anything to curb the temptations to masturbate or play video games

It was weird hanging with family last night and realizing how attached to phones we've become. I didn't know how to socialize with anyone, having been so reliant on my phone to fill the gap. And I watched everyone laser focused on the games on their phones instead of talking. Especially the kids. 

The process of growth always seems to feel in a way like detachment. Like at first, it's an attempt to separate yourself from those around you. Sometimes it takes an ego trick, like attempting to feel superior to them by treating yourself or your objectives as better, to kickstart it all. Like I begin now to really see how disorganized my mom is, or scared my dad is. Not in a like negative or resentful way, but in the sense that I know where I got those things from. Growing up here means distancing myself from those habits and allowing those to be a part of who I am publicly. 

I feel myself trying to become more of a man now. Maybe it's the perpetual horniness, but all I want is to smell like wood, be jacked, and have so much sex.

I don't need her to believe me. I don't need her to believe me. I don't need her to believe me for me to be valid. For my life to be valid. For my adversity to be valid.

Why do I want so badly for her to agree with me?

Because I need to be right. Because I want to fuck her so I need to say whatever it takes to win her over. Because if she doesn't agree with me then I'm invalid. Because if she, a beautiful women, doesn't validate me then no women will. **Because she mirrors my younger self and I'm trying to explain to her what I would've told myself, and I'm frustrated that I can't get through to her.** I'm fucking frustrated that I can't stop her from going the same way I did. From following the life that someone else set out for her. From being deluded into thinking money is everything. Money can't solve your heartbreak. Money won't stop a bear from attacking you. More money can't fix the pain you feel. You're a selfish fucking prick and the world will show that to you one way or another. 

It still doesn't fully explain the insecurity I feel.

I think it's like...if I can't prove to a 19 year old that I'm sure of what I'm doing, then am I doing the right thing? Resistance I believe. Idk. An 8 year old would think it's cool. An 80 year old would think it's brave. I think it's like that fear of going to the gym In a way. Someone who actually goes to the gym would cheer you on. You're only judged by the people who do nothing. She complains about the cold in 60 degree weather. So why should I care what she thinks? If she wants to complain about her feet hurting at Starbucks then let her. 

I think part of it is it feels like she's trying to control my beliefs. I defy the paradigm in her world of what it means to be successful and be happy, and I think it makes her uncomfortable. It feels like she's trying to put her beliefs onto me and i don't like being controlled that way. It feels like she's "trying to understand" but really just trying to convince and I hate that. Or maybe that's what I'm doing. I think I want her to like me, and for some reason it feels like the disagreement gets in the way. 

It feels frustrating and I'm holding onto it for whatever reason. 

It's like I need her to believe me. Or I need everyone to believe me. To believe in me. To understand me. Because then I don't have to deal with my own insecurities. Like I can stop them from running into the thorns by telling everyone to stop instead of removing the thorn. 

I want to let this go.

I think what I feel is guilt. For who I was when I was her age, and how I pushed so many people away by trying to convince them to be a part of my model. And I'm trying to save her from that as a way of fixing what happened to me. Because the loneliness I experience now has a lot to do with the way I treated people then.

There's two girls talking next to me. One is a runner, goes to the gym, extroverted, etc. why do I feel weird wanting to talk to them? Like eavesdrop and self-inclusion? Where did we develop this idea of privacy where people don't intrude on public conversations? Like I feel like the highest version of myself has no social barrier. Maybe it's the intention? Like they're beautiful.

There's a heightened sense of attraction almost constantly. I wonder if this is how others feel almost all the time. Like it makes sense why it would be easier for someone else to risk rejection if this is what they always feels like.

It's intriguing wondering what life may look like on the other side of this. Like has my "betrayal" mindset been a guilt from masturbation? Like was it tha way with Taylor and Jess? Forbidden fruit kind of thing? Has my life situation been reinforced over and over every time I've indulged in the fantasies? Has the numbness been much larger than I'd thought? Has my emotional turbulence in relationships been because it's the only time I wasn't numb, and didn't know how to handle those feelings? I wonder what the answer to all those questions might be. I immediately feel attracted to so may more peple

Even now, I feel that attraction that used to be reserved for relationships. Like that feeling the day after having sex with someone the first time. I feel it for a lot of people today. I want to kiss them all. I feel great love for them all. Is this what everyone else feels?

I think the way it works with the taboo stuff is it normalizes it. Like I wouldn't have to worry anymore about the way a family member kissing me would make me feel, because no longer would that mean I'd have to act on it. The discomfort of love would become normal and detached from sex.

It is interesting almost looking at the underlying urge in public. It's not the macrophilia so much as just being close to those body parts. Almost a childish way of undressing 

Put in other words: we were standing in line for an Amazon return. She must've been 23 at least. Indian, with black leggings, sparkly silver shoes, a black and white striped shirt with brown elbow pads, and a black puffy vest. Through the leggings, you could see the outlines of her buttcheeks. And when I looked at her shoes, I imagined at first I was under her feet. She knew I was down there. But she acted like it was nothing. The old fantasy from online came to mind of the Indian woman who cauterized the mini guy into her foot. But this woman was just playing with me. The more I looked at her, the less it was that. I'd look around her vagina and became her thong. Looked around her breasts and became her bra. The longer I looked, the less involved I was. It was more the feet, the breasts, the vagina, than it was about me being apart of it. Just mentally undressing her Like I'd imagined other people would do. I just wanted to desperately to see her feet, her thong, her bra, much moreso than I wanted the other things. To see her, and truly see her. She was beautiful. And to feel her.

That feeling of a new relationship is kinda huge now. Like an ever present feeling of excitement towards going in laying in bed as if I was coming home to having sex. Has everyone else felt this the whole time?
I'm only now beginning to realize the strength of this addiction.

The urges seem to exacerbate in public. At work rn and I feel this like persistent anxiety. I don't think it's as much I need to masturbate as it is the feeling even if I wanted to, I couldn't get away to do it. Feels like a hostage situation in that regards

But it also is occurring to me that maybe my issue is I'm surrounding myself with unfulfilled people 

Jazz exercise/meditation: Play autopilot and completely focus on individual parts (eg one time through just on piano, sax, bass, etc)

Definitely starting to flatline. The usual stuff wasn't really doing anything last night, and "what's the point" rang in my head. On the other side, I feel a lot less guilty now than before. More curious, creative, open minded. In a way I'm much more prone to connection. Talking to people is a bit easier, especially kids.

There's also a habitual pattern of confusing the things I want to do with how I feel in the moment, which is part of why it's so hard to engage in new things. Especially when I don't always feel great. Lack of discipline where the only solution is to do it anyways

There's a much stronger pull towards more real stimuli. Like being around certain people, seeing photos of that woman from mad men or even just Hoka shoes, it all turns me on. Not in a guilty way either. But the difficult part is pretty much anything makes me leak now

A woman just walked into the coffee shop I'm sitting in, and it's the first time I've noticed a full difference. I feel attracted to her with my entire body. It's not a fear, but a full body pull to talk to her, be intimate with her. Like it's not the fantasy dragging me to her. It's just her. It's so fucking refreshing. And it's like for the first time, o don't have to try to have a boner. I just have one. It makes me feel like before, all the times I was expecting one and didn't get one wasn't because I was misaligned, but instead because I should've had one and didn't from numbing or overuse. I don't feel scared of it, only charged by it. Like I could do anything with it. And it's real, not imaginary

Just now realizing I've been isolating. It's weird when I look at it, it's not intentional. It's a matter of priority I think. But making New Years plans is confusing because it's like I either stay up and hang out with people or wake up early and hike with people. It's like...idk. I want to do the second. Or like, I want to be around the type of people who do the second. But all the people I know are doing the first. It feels weird I'm doing the former. Like it's this weird paradox I guess? I don't really care about New Years all that much. For everyone around me it just seems like another reason to drink. And I wish it wasn't that. I wish the people around me wanted to wake up early and go hike instead, that I wasn't surrounded by the parties. It makes me feel crazy. And so I'm sitting in this space where I've been going against the edge for like weeks now, basically isolating because no one around me has even remotely close of a schedule. And I'm having to decide between what I want (hike) and what will socialize me (staying up). I think that's the nerve I hit a couple of weeks ago when sitting with my family. And all the connection stuff. It's not necessarily that I don't connect, it's that I live in a world that's isolating me.

Part of the isolation has been embarrassment. Anxiety around my life path. And honestly, it feels like I'm doing a lot to shape the world, not a lot to raise self esteem. Unless what I'm doing is raising self esteem? But also why should I care what they think? 

It's kinda like, if I don't have to talk about it, then I don't have to worry. If there's no one there to make fun of me, then I'm safe. And I realize I've moved somewhat far from the path I was wanting to lead, the person I was becoming before. I don't know if things were better, but there was a time I was more willing to take social risks. More willing to say "I'm a musician." Today, it feels hard to say that. And I haven't reaffirmed that in myself. So it feels like I'm trying to create a lot of circumstances to recover, or protect myself, from that.

It makes me think that routine is great, but getting out of routine is painful.
I feel harsh cynical and insecure

How do you decide the difference between avoiding conflict and choosing not to participate in drama? Brandi is coming at me talking about how I hang out with everyone except her. There's truth to this, I don't like being around her. 

I think I'm caught at a stand off where I can't tell what the version I want to be should do. There's the confrontational approach where I talk to her directly. Then there's the idea that maybe it's someone I just need to cut out

Definitely feeling a flatline now. There's certain things I grasp onto, but for the most part I feel indifferent. There's a much deeper attraction in person, and also a detraction from certain people.

I AM an authority in music. It's time for me to decide that I make music my friends enjoy. 

I'm at this critical point where getting better at music and life is no longer about practicing in isolation so much as it is bringing what I've learned to places where I can use these things as tools for connection. And I begin to realize the distance between what I have and what I want is summed by the way I feel around my friends. I want to be around beautiful people who find the joy in anything.

Simultaneously, I've begun realizing that I can't change the world, but the energy I carry changes everyone around me. My mental health practices have begun to extend beyond myself and into the people around me, and the more I commit to being the truest and best version of myself, the more joy I and the people around me experience. I become an authority by committing to my values and allowing others to participate in the joy I experience because of it. 

Everything I do tha betters my life sets an example for everyone else. When I meditate and talk about it, people around me meditate. When I adventure, they adventure. When I plan and prepare, so do they. When I run, so do they. When I love Music with all that I can, they do too. When I quit social media, so will they. When I quit gaming so will they. When I make more of an effort to be apart of their world, so will they. Everything starts with me. 

When I believe that I'm already the best version of myself and remembering how I got there, then they will too. You can't teach, all you can do is show. They will learn when they see your results. You can't change them, but you can create an impact so dense that they fall in.

Visualize what it feels like to be around them.

I think the energy drain really is an illusion of Resistance. It's 11:29. I woke up at 5:15, ran, and meditated, and I feel great. Joyful and at peace. Even more accomplished for having done those things.

Gotten to a point in bebop where it's gonna be much more beneficial if I just play along to tunes, zone out from the drummer, and follow the leader. Starting to notice today how the energy and feel changes better playing alongside it than playing note for note

Actually, noticing this more outside of Bebop too. Was jamming to Undertale stuff to compare against earlier this year, and the most distinctive things i noticed was that now I have a much stronger attention to holding the groove steady. There isn't as much filling around as there is just trying to groove with the song and fit my part, which is a huge advancement. Doing so has made me realize though how little I actually know about fill work. Like most my fills are pretty half ass and barely have any set up. Also a lack of syncopation in important parts. But the fills are an important part. I'm beginning to see how it could be possible to FEEL like how Snarky Puppy must feel all the time by just playing the right parts and listening intently. Definitely need to groove better and listen better
Show up consistently. To the jam, to the club, etc. let the relationships flourish naturally. Be comfortable with beginnings. Gradual growth.

Realize that friendships aren't forced. They're a consequence of repeated exposure. Go there, be yourself, and attract naturally. 

You weren't friends with everyone at Starbucks on the first day. Same with PMA. And drumline. It's too much pressure to expect us to show up and automatically be the most gregarious person there. That comes with time.

It almost seems like there's a correlation between gaining weight and the more self-erasing fantasies. Like, knowing that I use weight as a way to be more invisible, I gain weight whenever the fantasies are more about being objectified

There's a new ideal of wishing I had ear training. Wishing I could hear the chord progressions and knowing them immediately, then being able to play on any instrument (really piano or guitar) then plopping down on that instrument and play it. It's not the highest priority, especially with all the changes I've been making. But eventually it will be one

Attraction to footwear declined today. It's there but not charging.

My spaces are all littered with unnecessary garbage that needs to be cleaned out. Bedroom and basement included.

Watching old drum videos, it's obvious I used to play drums and not Music. So much overplaying, so little to grab onto. Even my most recent practices, there's a growing awareness of when I lose the groove, and how often fills leave the groove behind
